However, the threat from within is no less grave. A contract employee who was found hunting a spotted deer using dogs was first suspended and later taken back on the job, a student alleged. In a 2012, case of deer poaching a student too was apprehended for helping his friends from outside to hunt, a forest official who did not want to be identified said.UoH administration, has, however, decided to start an awareness drive on campus. “We have regular patrolling which target poachers. We will intensify the patrolling and also set up separate squads to deal with the issue,” said A. Appa Rao, Vice Chancellor University of Hyderabad.